## MDC File Structure

Every `.mdc` file must follow this structure:

```markdown
---
description: USE WHEN [clear trigger condition]
globs: 
  - "pattern1"
  - "pattern2"
alwaysApply: false
---

# [Descriptive Title]

**Purpose:** [One-sentence explanation of what this rule covers]

---

## [Major Section]

[Explanation paragraph]

```[language]
// ❌ Wrong: [Why this is wrong]
[bad example code]

// ✅ Correct: [Why this is right]
[good example code]
```

## [Next Section]

...
```

### Frontmatter Requirements

**`description` field (required for Agent Requested rules):**
- Start with "USE WHEN" for clarity
- Be specific about trigger conditions
- Use action-based language

```yaml
# ✅ Good descriptions
description: USE WHEN writing or modifying React components
description: USE WHEN handling authentication or user sessions
description: USE WHEN creating API endpoints or routes
description: USE WHEN writing test files

# ❌ Bad descriptions
description: React rules
description: Security stuff
description: General standards
```

**`globs` field (required for Auto Attached rules):**
- Use specific patterns to avoid over-attachment
- Test patterns to ensure they match intended files

```yaml
# ✅ Good globs - specific targeting
globs: 
  - "**/*.test.ts"
  - "**/*.test.tsx"
  - "**/*.spec.ts"

# ✅ Good globs - framework-specific
globs:
  - "**/app/**/*.tsx"      # Next.js App Router
  - "**/pages/**/*.tsx"    # Next.js Pages Router

# ❌ Bad globs - too broad
globs:
  - "**/*"                 # Matches everything
  - "*.ts"                 # Misses nested files

# ❌ Bad globs - missing related extensions
globs:
  - "**/*.tsx"             # Missing .jsx
```

**`alwaysApply` field:**
- Set `true` for **core universal standards only**
- Maximum 1-2 rules should use `alwaysApply: true`
- Most rules should be `false` (auto-attached or agent-requested)

```yaml
# ✅ Appropriate alwaysApply: true
# File: core.mdc
alwaysApply: true  # Universal behavior standards

# ✅ Appropriate alwaysApply: false  
# File: react.mdc
alwaysApply: false  # Only needed for React files

# ❌ Wrong: Too many alwaysApply
# If 5+ rules have alwaysApply: true, you're bloating context
```

