## Organizing Rules Across Files

### Single Responsibility Per File

Each rule file should cover one coherent domain:

```
✅ Good organization:
├── typescript.mdc        # All TS type system rules
├── react-components.mdc  # Component structure, props, JSX
├── react-hooks.mdc       # Hook-specific patterns
└── react-state.mdc       # State management patterns

❌ Bad organization:
├── rules1.mdc            # Random mix of TS and React rules
├── frontend.mdc          # Too broad - TS, React, CSS, HTML
└── myRules.mdc           # Non-descriptive name
```

### Nested Rules for Features

**Use subdirectories for feature-specific rules:**

```
.cursor/rules/
├── core.mdc
├── typescript.mdc
├── react.mdc
└── features/
    ├── auth/
    │   └── auth.mdc          # Auth-specific patterns
    ├── payments/
    │   └── stripe.mdc        # Payment integration rules
    └── admin/
        └── admin-ui.mdc      # Admin-specific UI patterns
```

**Nested rules automatically apply when files in that directory are referenced.**

