## Migration from Legacy .cursorrules

**If you have an existing `.cursorrules` file:**

```bash
# 1. Create new directory structure
mkdir -p .cursor/rules

# 2. Split .cursorrules into focused files
# - Universal standards → core.mdc (alwaysApply: true)
# - Language-specific → typescript.mdc, javascript.mdc
# - Framework-specific → react.mdc, vue.mdc
# - Domain-specific → testing.mdc, api-design.mdc

# 3. Add frontmatter to each file
# See structure section above

# 4. Test each rule file individually

# 5. Optional: Keep .cursorrules for backward compatibility
# Or delete once migration confirmed working
```

**Migration checklist:**

- [ ] Created `.cursor/rules/` directory
- [ ] Split rules into focused files (<500 lines each)
- [ ] Added proper frontmatter to all files
- [ ] Included code examples for abstract rules
- [ ] Tested each rule file activates correctly
- [ ] Updated glob patterns for accuracy
- [ ] Removed duplicated guidance across files
- [ ] Committed changes with migration notes

