## Best Practices Summary

**DO:**
- ✅ Create focused, single-responsibility rule files
- ✅ Use "USE WHEN" in descriptions for Agent Requested rules
- ✅ Include concrete code examples (✅ ❌ pattern)
- ✅ Explain the "why" behind rules
- ✅ Test rules with actual file changes
- ✅ Keep individual files under 500 lines
- ✅ Use specific glob patterns
- ✅ Version control your rules
- ✅ Review and update rules regularly

**DON'T:**
- ❌ Create generic, catch-all rule files
- ❌ Write abstract principles without examples
- ❌ Duplicate guidance across multiple files
- ❌ Use overly broad glob patterns (`**/*`)
- ❌ Set `alwaysApply: true` on most rules
- ❌ Include outdated framework patterns
- ❌ Create rules for temporary situations
- ❌ Forget to test rules after editing

